CUSTOMER SEGMENTATION USING K-MEANS CLUSTERING

1. INTRODUCTION

Customer segmentation is the process of dividing customers into groups based on their purchasing behavior. Businesses use segmentation to improve marketing strategies and customer satisfaction.

2. OBJECTIVE

• Understand customer data
• Apply clustering techniques
• Identify customer groups

3. DATASET DESCRIPTION

The dataset contains:
• Customer ID
• Gender
• Age
• Annual Income
• Spending Score

4. METHODOLOGY

Step 1: Data Collection

Step 2: Data Preprocessing

Step 3: Feature Selection

Step 4: K-Means Clustering

Step 5: Cluster Visualization

Step 6: Result Analysis

5. RESULTS

Five customer groups were identified:

• High Income – High Spending
• High Income – Low Spending
• Medium Income – Medium Spending
• Low Income – High Spending
• Low Income – Low Spending

6. BUSINESS INSIGHTS

Customer segmentation helps businesses target customers more effectively and improve marketing decisions.

7. CONCLUSION

K-Means clustering successfully grouped customers according to their purchasing behavior.
